Day 12

Here’s a step-by-step guide to create a free Azure DevOps account and a new project:

✅ Step 1: Create a Free Azure DevOps Account
🌐 Go to: https://dev.azure.com/

Sign in with your Microsoft account (or create one if needed).

Once signed in, you’ll be redirected to the Azure DevOps welcome page.


✅ Step 2: Create a New Azure DevOps Organization (first time only)
Click "Create new organization".

Enter:

Organization name: e.g., harshana-devops

Region: choose a location close to you.

Click Continue.


✅ Step 3: Create a New Project
Click “New Project” on the dashboard.

Fill in project details:

Project name: e.g., DevOps-Practice

Description (optional): “Learning DevOps step by step”

Visibility: choose Private (recommended) or Public

Version control: Git (default)

Work item process: Basic

Click Create.


✅ Your Azure DevOps project is ready! You can now:

Create repositories

Build CI/CD pipelines

Use Boards for task tracking

Integrate with GitHub or VS Code
